# Melt RLum-class objects into a flat data.frame

Melt RLum-class objects into a flat data.frame

## Usage

``` r
melt_RLum(object, ...)

# S4 method for class 'list'
melt_RLum(object, ...)

# S4 method for class 'RLum.Analysis'
melt_RLum(object)

# S4 method for class 'RLum.Data.Curve'
melt_RLum(object)
```

## Arguments

- object:

  [RLum](https://r-lum.github.io/Luminescence/reference/RLum-class.md)
  (**required**): S4 object of class `RLum`

- ...:

  further arguments passed to the specific class method

## Value

A flat [data.frame](https://rdrr.io/r/base/data.frame.html).

## Functions

- `melt_RLum(list)`: Returns a list of melted
  [RLum](https://r-lum.github.io/Luminescence/reference/RLum-class.md)
  objects; non-RLum objects are silently removed.

- `melt_RLum(RLum.Analysis)`: Melts
  [RLum.Analysis](https://r-lum.github.io/Luminescence/reference/RLum.Analysis-class.md)
  objects into a flat data.frame with columns `X`, `Y`, `TYPE`, `UID`,
  to be used in combination with other packages such as `ggplot2`.

- `melt_RLum(RLum.Data.Curve)`: Melts
  [RLum.Data.Curve](https://r-lum.github.io/Luminescence/reference/RLum.Data.Curve-class.md)
  objects into a flat data.frame with columns `X`, `Y`, `TYPE`, `UID`,
  to be used in combination with other packages such as `ggplot2`.
